<text>Accessing an angular bond&apos;s properties

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

To access a radial bond&apos;s properties, double-click it when the model container is in the selection mode (i.e. the button &quot; &quot; is chosen), and then you will see the following dialog window:

  
&#12304;This is a screenshot.&#12305;

This dialog box allows you to change the bond angle and strength.

Script support

To change an angular bond&apos;s properties, use the set command. For example, set abond[0].strength 100 sets the strength of the first angular bond. Currently, only two properties of an angular bond are settable through scripts: strength and bondangle. 

To change multiple angular bonds&apos; properties, select them first and then call set strength [value] to change their strengths and set bondangle [value] to change their bond angles.

